<h2 align="center" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 255);"><big>Structure of an
Enterprise Bean (Contd)...<br>
</big></h2>
<h3 style="margin-top: 6px; margin-bottom: 0pt" align="justify"><font color="#FF00FF"><big><big>XML
Deployment Descriptor</big></big></font></h3>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p style="margin-top: 6px; margin-bottom: 0pt" align="justify"><font size="5">An
    XML file (<i><a href="http://www.w3c.org/XML">www.w3c.org/XML</a></i>) that
    contains configuration information and properties of the bean:</font></p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p style="margin-top: 6px; margin-bottom: 0pt" align="justify"><i><font size="5">Information
        about the component's classes</font></i></p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p style="margin-top: 6px; margin-bottom: 0pt" align="justify"><i><font size="5">Transactional
        attributes</font></i></p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p style="margin-top: 6px; margin-bottom: 0pt" align="justify"><i><font size="5">Security
        Roles</font></i></p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p style="margin-top: 6px; margin-bottom: 0pt" align="justify"><i><font size="5">Settings
        that dictate the component's behavior</font></i></p>
      </li>
    </ul>
        <p style="margin-top: 6px; margin-bottom: 0pt" align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p style="margin-top: 6px; margin-bottom: 0pt" align="justify"><font size="5">Two
    beans with identical EJBHomes, EJBObjects and bean classes but different&nbsp;
    deployment descriptors are considered as two different beans.</font></p>
  </li>
</ul>
</body>
